# learndl — Project-specific rules

## Project overview
Chinese A-share equity quantitative research system: data acquisition, factor research, NN/boost/GP model training, backtesting, and simulation trading.

## Repository layout
```
learndl/
├── pyproject.toml          # metadata & dependencies (uv-managed)
├── launch.py               # start Streamlit interactive app
├── configs/                # all YAML configuration (see below)
├── src/                    # source code (see below)
├── scripts/                # numbered pipeline scripts (0–7)
├── context/                # living documentation vault (Obsidian-compatible)
├── runs/                   # .bat / .sh shell helpers
├── resources/              # shared code resources
├── templates/              # html / css / img / font
├── data/                   # raw & processed data (not synced)
├── models/                 # trained model checkpoints (not synced)
├── results/                # exports & analysis output (not synced)
├── logs/                   # log files (not synced)
├── .local_resources/       # local-only assets (not synced)
└── .secret/                # secrets (not synced)
```

## Source layout (`src/`)
```
src/
├── proj/         # infrastructure: env/, cal/, db/, log/, util/, core/
├── func/         # numerical utils: basic.py, tensor.py, transform.py, metric.py
├── data/         # data pipeline: crawler/, download/, loader/, preprocess/, update/, util/
├── res/
│   ├── factor/   # factor engine: calculator/, defs/, analytic/, fmp/, loader/, risk/, util/
│   ├── algo/     # algo modules: nn/ (architectures), boost/ (LightGBM/XGBoost/CatBoost)
│   ├── model/    # training framework: callback/, data_module/, model_module/, util/
│   ├── gp/       # genetic programming: func/, param/, util/
│   └── trading/  # portfolio construction & trading: util/
├── api/          # stable public facade: data, factor, model, trading, update, summary
└── interactive/  # Streamlit app: backend/, frontend/, main/
```

## Config layout (`configs/`)
```
configs/
├── algo/
│   ├── nn/           # per-architecture hyperparams (gru.yaml, tra.yaml, patch_tst.yaml, …)
│   ├── boost/        # boost params (lgbm.yaml, xgboost.yaml, catboost.yaml, ada.yaml)
│   └── gp/           # GP evolution params (params.yaml)
├── model/
│   ├── schedule/     # training schedules — primary entry point for model training
│   ├── default/      # default field values (required.yaml, optional.yaml)
│   ├── model.yaml    # model architecture config
│   ├── train.yaml    # training loop config
│   ├── callbacks.yaml
│   ├── input.yaml
│   ├── env.yaml
│   └── conditional.yaml
├── setting/
│   ├── model.yaml         # project model settings
│   └── trading_port.yaml  # portfolio specifications (NOT configs/trading/)
├── preference/       # app preferences (project, interactive, logger, shell_opener)
└── util/
    ├── factor/       # factor opt configs, risk_factors.yaml
    ├── industry/     # industry classification (tushare.yaml)
    ├── transform/    # preprocessing params
    └── calendar/     # trading day overrides
```

## Key classes and entry points
| Purpose | Class / Object | Import path |
|---------|----------------|-------------|
| Paths | `PATH` | `src.proj.env` |
| Machine config | `MACHINE` | `src.proj.env` |
| Trading calendar | `CALENDAR` | `src.proj.cal` |
| DB I/O | `df_io`, `DBPath` | `src.proj.db` |
| Logging | `Logger` | `src.proj.log` |
| Constants | `CONST` | `src.proj.env` |
| Data access | `TRADE`, `BS`, `IS`, `CF`, `MKLINE`, … | `src.data` |
| Data API | `DataAPI` | `src.api.data` |
| Factor calc | `FactorCalculator` (base) | `src.res.factor.calculator` |
| Factor API | `FactorAPI` | `src.api.factor` |
| Model API | `ModelAPI` | `src.api.model` |
| Trading API | `TradingAPI` | `src.api.trading` |
| Script tools | `ScriptTool`, `Options` | `src.proj.util` |

## Logging
Always use `src.proj.log.Logger` — never `print()` or stdlib `logging` directly.

## Path conventions
- **Never hardcode paths.** Use `PATH.xxx` from `src.proj.env.path`.
- All paths derive from `MACHINE.data_root` (set in machine config).

## Data and factors
- Correctness first; re-verify when changing data paths or transforms.
- Prefer vectorization and torch/polars when it clearly pays off; otherwise pandas.
- Data access: use `DateDataAccess` singletons (`TRADE`, `BS`, `MKLINE`, …) or `DataAPI`.
- Raw data I/O: `src.proj.db` (`df_io.save`, `df_io.load`) — feather/parquet format.
- Factors: follow patterns under `src.res.factor` — subclass `FactorCalculator`, implement `calculate(data: DataBlock) -> DataBlock`. Auto-registered by metaclass.
- Respect existing cleaning choices: forward-fill → winsorize → industry neutralize → z-score.
- Point-in-time discipline for fundamental data: use `BS.qtr()` / `BS.ttm()`, never period-end raw values.

## Model training
- Entry: `ModelAPI.schedule_model(schedule_name)` — schedule configs live in `configs/model/schedule/`.
- Do not instantiate NN/boost classes directly; go through `AlgoModule` / `ModelAPI`.
- New architectures: subclass `BaseNNModel` in `src/res/algo/nn/`, implement `forward(batch: BatchInput)` — auto-registered by class name.

## Backtesting and strategies
- Model all trading costs: commission, slippage, stamp duty, suspension limits.
- No lookahead: only information available at decision time.

## Script conventions
Every file in `scripts/` must have a YAML header block (lines starting with `#`, terminated by a blank line) that is parseable by `ScriptHeader.read_from_file()`:
```python
# coding: utf-8
# author: ...
# date: YYYY-MM-DD
# description: Short title
# content: Longer description
# email: True | False
# mode: shell | os
# parameters:
#   param_name:
#       type: str | int | float | bool | [opt1, opt2] | Options.available_xxx()
#       desc: explanation
#       required: True | False
#       default: value
```
Wrap `main()` with `@ScriptTool(task_name)` for task tracking, locking, and email.

## Interactive app
- Start: `uv run launch.py`
- Scripts visible to the app: numbered folders only (files/dirs starting with `.` or `_` are hidden).
- `Options.available_xxx()` methods provide dynamic dropdowns from the `options_cache.json`.

## Context library
Full module documentation is in `context/`. See `context/CLAUDE.md` for the index.
When a doc is found to be wrong, add `<!-- STALE: reason -->` inline and run:
```bash
uv run scripts/0_check/2_update_context.py --mode stale
```

## Data fetching policy
Ask the human before any new external scrape or introducing a new data provider.

## Repository hygiene
Do not suggest committing paths under `.local_resources/` or `.secret/` to git.

## Post-edit checks (substantive code changes)
```bash
ruff check src scripts
pyright src scripts
```
